HEADWORD: Propylene
<hw>Pro"pyl*ene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>propyl⟦egrave⟧ne</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A colorless
gaseous hydrocarbon (<chform>C3H6</chform>) of the ethylene series,
having a garlic odor. It occurs in coal gas, and is produced
artificially in various ways. Called also
<altname>propene</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

